HEADWORD: Periosteum
<hw>Per`i*os"te*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>perio`steos</grk> round the bones; <grk>peri`</grk> around +
<grk>'oste`on</grk> a bone: cf. L. <ets>periosteon</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The membrane of fibrous connective tissue which
closely invests all bones except at the articular surfaces.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Periostitis</ent>⟦br⟧
